<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-3562dbd6be8fbc67da4a652b1718b46008d682e5">Orc Town</h2>
<p>
<a href="./OrcTown">OrcTown</a> is a <a href="./SpecialLevel">SpecialLevel</a> on CL35 of Moria. It is not persistent. <a href="./Spoilers_2fDungeons_2fOrcTown_2fMap">/Map</a> 
</p>
<p>
Guardian: Bolg, son of Azog. 
</p>
<p>
Guaranteed artifact: The <a class="interwiki" title="Self" href="./Spoilers_2fArtifacts_2fStone_20of_20Lore"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-inter.png" alt="[Self]" height="16" width="16">Stone of Lore</a>, which lies top-center of the map.  
</p>
<p>
Recommended:  
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 fire resistance (there is a narrow lava moat) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 monster detection 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 speed 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 CCW / healing 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
Useful: 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 A ranged attack spell which can cross glass walls (e.g. Mindwave) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The 'dunna hrassa' floor inscription is very handy for crowd control, especially if you are a warrior type. (Just make sure you have levitation or flying, first!) 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
Warnings:  
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 The Orc Town is heavily populated.  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 When you first arrive in Orc Town, there will be several Shrieker Mushrooms very close to you. Kill them as fast as possible. More Shriekers are scattered throughout the level, in positions chosen to place you in as much danger as possible. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
The room to the northeast of your arrival place is chock full of monsters. There is a Shrieker behind a glass panel which is aimed at this room. You need to go straight north, then right, then down and through a hidden wall in order to get at it. 
</p>
<p>
There are a number of hidden passages in the walls in Orc Town. You will not be able to detect them, but you can test for it by trying to walk into the wall, or by some means of detection, watching to see monsters moving through them. 
</p>
<p>
You may have trouble getting at the <a class="interwiki" title="Self" href="./Spoilers_2fArtifacts_2fStone_20of_20Lore"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-inter.png" alt="[Self]" height="16" width="16">Stone of Lore</a>. Try looking for hidden passages and void jumpgates. If it's difficult for you, you can check the <a href="./Spoilers_2fDungeons_2fOrcTown_2fMap">/Map</a>. 
</p>
<p>
Good luck! 
</p>
<p>
<strong>Spoiler</strong> 
</p>
<p>
If you have gained the corruption Sarumans power, then via telekinesis you may steal the stone through the glass wall, thus making your presence in the town shorter. But usually theres a nice unique in the room with the void gate, so i'd advise to search for it instead of "cheating" the level:) 
</p>

    <ul>

 <strong><a href="./ErintiAkairis">ErintiAkairis</a></strong>: That corruption is specific to Theme and any other modules using that extended corruption list. The Orc Town level isn't. (Telekinesis can be had other ways, yes, but still.) </ul>

